notesStmt.note: Title from added title (second flyleaf recto at front of book).

msContents.summary: Verse by verse commentary of Ḥāfiẓ's Dīvān written in at least two hands on two different types of paper.

supportDesc.extent: ii, 341, ii leaves : 196 x 143 (160 x 95) mm, bound to 198 x 151 mm

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 23 long lines; catchwords every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in two styles. One portion in naskh with elements of nastaʻlīq in black ink (f. 7-203); pointed. The other portion in nastaʻlīq in black ink (f. 1-6, 204-341); pointed.

binding.p: Bound in paper over paperboard with light brown leather spine and edges; paper sides have a grid pattern of dots with a five-pronged design set into a red field.

origin.p: The copy is undated; probably produced in the 18th or 19th century.
